lead_paragraph: Candice Dupree had 20 points and 6 rebounds to help the host Chicago Sky beat the Liberty, 78-73, last night. The Sky went on a 12-4 run to open the fourth quarter, taking a 66-56 lead with 4 minutes 58 seconds remaining, then made 10 of 12 free throws in the final minute. Becky Hammon scored 18 points for the Liberty (4-13), which lost its fourth in a row.
